  "instructions": [
    "Set a large non\u2011stick skillet over medium heat and add 1\u202ftbsp olive oil.",
    "Slice the cod into bite\u2011size cubes, season lightly with salt and \u00bd\u202ftsp pepper.",
    "Add the cod to the skillet, cook for 3\u202fmin, then flip and cook another 2\u202fmin until just opaque.",
    "Remove cod and set aside; add remaining 1\u202ftbsp oil to the skillet.",
    "Saut\u00e9 the sumac, dill, capers, parsley, coriander, and a splash of lemon juice for 30\u202fsec until fragrant.",
    "Return the cod to the pan, pour in the honey, then sprinkle nutmeg and remaining pepper, tossing gently to coat.",
    "Cook for an additional 2\u202fmin, allowing flavors to meld and the cod to finish cooking.",
    "Remove from heat, drizzle with the remaining 1\u202ftbsp olive oil, and toast sesame seeds in a dry skillet for 1\u202fmin before sprinkling on top.",
    "Serve hot with a side of steamed vegetables or a light salad.",
